comment: * API for inquiring about the general status of the provider.

variables.name: CONTENT_URI
variables.comment:
* The content:// style URI for this table.  Requests to this URI can be
         * performed on the UI thread because they are always unblocking.

variables.name: CONTENT_TYPE
variables.comment:
* The MIME-type of {@link #CONTENT_URI} providing a directory of
         * settings.

variables.name: STATUS
variables.comment: * An integer representing the current status of the provider.

variables.name: STATUS_BUSY
variables.comment:
* The provider won't respond to queries. It is in the middle of a long running task, such
         * as a database upgrade or locale change.

variables.name: STATUS_EMPTY
variables.comment:
* The status that indicates that there are no accounts and no contacts
         * on the device.

variables.name: DATABASE_CREATION_TIMESTAMP
variables.comment:
* Timestamp (milliseconds since epoch) of when the provider's database was created. * *

Type: long
